"Using a pastry brush, brush surface of lamb with honey and place onto Varoma tray."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and weigh potatoes into it. Place Varoma tray with lamb into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma tray, transfer lamb onto a plate and cover to keep warm. Secure Varoma lid and steam potatoes <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Place Varoma tray back into position, weigh spinach onto it, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Remove Varoma and set aside. Place a large non-stick frying pan over medium-high heat and add 1 tbsp of the oil. Add cooked potatoes, season with salt and pepper. Smash potatoes down with the back of a spoon and fry for 10-12 minutes, or until golden. Transfer into a serving bowl and sprinkle with parsley. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place butter, reserved spinach, cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg into mixing bowl and cook <b>2 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>, then blend <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and blend <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>. Set aside in mixing bowl and keep warm."},{"content":"Press reserved Parmesan crust onto lamb cutlets. Place non-stick frying pan over medium heat and add oil. Fry cutlets on both sides (approx. 1-2 minutes each side) until golden, carefully turning once (ensure crust stays on lamb). Serve lamb with spinach and potatoes."}],"hintsAndTricks":["French trimmed lamb cutlets mean that the protruding bone has been stripped of meat and sinew for a neater presentation.You can trim the cutlets yourself or ask your butcher to do it for you.","Use oregano or mint instead of parsley.","Any potato can be used instead of kipfler potatoes; simply cut into pieces (3 cm).","The lamb is steamed to medium-rare in this recipe; if you prefer your lamb cooked a bit longer, steam <strong>14 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong>."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","1h 15m","2 portions"]}